cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Tessera: A Mid-Frequency ML Trading System for Crypto Perpetual Futures"
abstract: >
  Tessera is an end-to-end, publicly reproducible mid-frequency ML trading
  system for USDT-margined crypto perpetual futures on Binance and Bybit.
  It covers raw OHLCV ingestion, microstructure feature engineering
  (VPIN, OFI, microprice), triple-barrier labeling (AFML §3),
  uniqueness-weighted samples (AFML §4), LightGBM primary and meta-label
  models, PatchTST and Chronos zero-shot baselines, Combinatorial Purged
  Cross-Validation, deflated Sharpe validation, a quarter-Kelly risk stack
  with circuit breakers, and Nautilus Trader live paper trading.
