  - algorithmic trading
  - cryptocurrency
  - perpetual futures
  - time series
  - financial machine learning
  - microstructure
  - LightGBM
  - meta-labeling
  - Nautilus Trader

# ── Zenodo deposit instructions (manual — do not automate) ─────────────────
#
# 1. Ensure a GitHub release exists at the target version tag (e.g. v0.1.0).
# 2. Go to https://zenodo.org and connect your GitHub account.
# 3. Enable the Tessera repository under "GitHub" in Zenodo settings.
# 4. Push the release tag to GitHub — Zenodo will automatically create a
#    deposit and assign a DOI.
# 5. Update this file: add the doi field below.
# 6. Update paper/main.tex to include the Zenodo DOI in the citation.
